<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
    <title>{{title}}</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="main-content">
        {{>header}}
        <h2>Help & FAQ</h2>
        <h3>How to use the weather app?</h3>
        <p>Simply enter a location in the search box on the home page and click "Search". You'll get the current weather forecast for that location.</p>
        <h3>What locations are supported?</h3>
        <p>You can search for cities, towns, or any valid location address.</p>
        <h3>Having trouble?</h3>
        <p>Make sure your location is spelled correctly and try again. If issues persist, contact support.</p>
    </div>
    {{>footer}}
</body>
</html>